<div><div><h2>The biggest change after the Panama Papers? The one inside people\xe2\x80\x99s heads</h2></div><div>two years after the panama papers was first published journalists look back on the project through different lenses but taken together they reflect a world in flux. the <a href="https://www.icij.org/investigations/panama-papers/">panama papers</a> investigation deposed heads of governments and resulted in the recovery of hundreds of millions of dollars. but it also changed the the worldwide understanding of a cleverly contrived and continuously <a href="https://www.icij.org/investigations/panama-papers/stairway-tax-heaven/">evolving system</a> that swells and protects the riches of the wealthy and powerful. the journalists who worked on the panama papers look back on the project through different lenses but taken together they reflect a world in flux. <a href="https://twitter.com/sol_lauria lang=en">sol laur\xc3\xada</a> an argentinian journalist who has worked in panama since 2013 witnessed the panama papers up close like few others. laur\xc3\xada said that one of her strongest memories during the months before publication is \xe2\x80\x9cseeing the evidence -such as documents emails or messages with [offshore lawyer ramon] fonseca&#8217;s own handwriting- of information that we already knew but had never been able to prove due to the lack of access to the information in offshore jurisdictions.\xe2\x80\x9d in 2017 laur\xc3\xada nabbed a rare three-hour interview with mossack fonseca co-founder fonseca in his apartment in panama city. \xe2\x80\x9cask what you want\xe2\x80\x9d fonseca said to laur\xc3\xada who has written a profile on the offshore lawyer for an upcoming book. fonseca writes laur\xc3\xada \xe2\x80\x9cis a man of medium and resounding stature who lost several pounds after the panama papers. he exercises with a personal trainer every day after a routine that he clings to as his only defense: from an early hour he checks to see if he has been sued in some corner of the world then reads and later tries to write.\xe2\x80\x9d on the couch in a small dark room fonseca told laur\xc3\xada that there was a lot of sensationalism in the panama papers. &#8220;you do not regret anything &#8221; laur\xc3\xada asked. \xe2\x80\x9cno\xe2\x80\x9d fonseca replied. \xe2\x80\x9cwe take risks of course because everything in life is risk. but we did nothing illegal.\xe2\x80\x9d laur\xc3\xada wrote that fonseca\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x9cverbiage at times is dark at times graceful or melancholy. when he speaks of panama papers he is always unrepentant as if seeking to shield himself with repetition.\xe2\x80\x9d &#8220;i consider myself a balanced man\xe2\x80\x9d fonseca replied. \xe2\x80\x9ci hardly regret it. i know that i am not perfect but i do not have an enormous ego.\xe2\x80\x9d &#8220;do you not find anything questionable however lawful &#8221; laur\xc3\xada asked again &#8220;but everyone does it! everyone uses the system!\xe2\x80\x9d fonseca told laur\xc3\xada. \xe2\x80\x9cthe world&#8217;s savior does not understand that the capitalist world is managed by corporations. the world does not subsist with the state bureaucracy. and we can\xe2\x80\x99t stop encouraging those who want to create wealth create business create ideas. please\xe2\x80\xa6\xe2\x80\x9d despite fonseca\xe2\x80\x99s protestations and after some pushback from the government of panama that initially claimed it too had done little wrong laur\xc3\xada sees some changes. panamanian authorities sanctioned delinquent offshore companies with financial penalties and closed down more than 275000 offshore companies. new rules long-resisted require panama to collect and swap certain financial information with other governments. \xe2\x80\x9cwe will see how it is implemented\xe2\x80\x9d laur\xc3\xada said. while panama looked to update its laws in other nations it was the lawmakers themselves facing public scrutiny over their finances. after 15 months of protests lawsuits and vitriolic online debates across pakistan prime minister <a href="https://www.icij.org/investigations/panama-papers/20170728-pakistan-pm-disqualified/">nawaz sharif stepped down</a> from power in july 2017. sharif was the second prime minister to lose office because of the panama papers following the more rapid departure of iceland\xe2\x80\x99s leader <a href="https://www.icij.org/investigations/panama-papers/20160403-iceland-prime-minister/">sigmundur dav\xc3\xad\xc3\xb0 gunnlaugsson</a>. <a href="https://www.icij.org/journalists/umar-cheema/">umar cheema</a> an investigative journalist with <a href="https://www.thenews.com.pk/">the news</a> in pakistan led reporting on the offshore holdings of sharif\xe2\x80\x99s family members. cheema said that the panama papers was \xe2\x80\x9ca tour through the underworld of the rich\xe2\x80\x9d that has left a permanent mark on him. \xe2\x80\x9cthey enjoy all the privileges milk all the benefits and rig the policies\xe2\x80\x9d cheema said. \xe2\x80\x9cnevertheless they park wealth abroad.\xe2\x80\x9d <a href="https://www.icij.org/journalists/bastian-obermayer/">bastian obermayer</a> is the german journalist who received the first message from <a href="https://www.icij.org/investigations/panama-papers/20160506-john-doe-statement/">john doe</a> the anonymous whistleblower who provided s\xc3\xbcddeutsche zeitung with the data for the panama papers. obermayer and his colleague <a href="https://www.icij.org/journalists/frederik-obermaier/">frederik obermaier</a> chose to share the <a href="https://www.icij.org/investigations/panama-papers/20160403-panama-papers-global-overview/">11.4 million documents</a> with the international consortium of journalists (icij) on the understanding icij would assemble a <a href="https://www.icij.org/investigations/panama-papers/pages/media-partners/">coalition of reporters</a> around the world. asked about what the biggest change is since the project obermayer points to two things. \xe2\x80\x9calthough there\xe2\x80\x99s even a new anti-offshore law in germany that\xe2\x80\x99s called the \xe2\x80\x9cpanama plan\xe2\x80\x9d obermayer said \xe2\x80\x9ci think the biggest change is that people are aware now of the menace that the anonymous offshore world poses.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9cthe biggest change is the one in the heads.\xe2\x80\x9d</div></div>